The paper proposes a new attention-based model for AMR parsing, which is a task in computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The model also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions experimental results that involve natural language processing and semantic analysis, which could also make it relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a subfield of natural language processing.
